textBox.richText: Biography: I was born and raised in Kingwood, TX. While an undergraduate at Texas A&M, I worked in Dr. Daniel Singleton's lab with a focus on measuring kinetic isotope effect data in order to study the mechanism of Diels-Alder reactions. I graduated with a B.S. in Chemistry in 2015 and joined the Anslyn group shortly thereafter. Research: I am studying the reversibility of dynamic covalent bonds in a tri-component assembly.
